  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><em><strong>Artillery.</strong></em> </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">To use the weapon to attack you must not have made any movement since the start of the turn and, to be able to move with the weapon, you must use an action. The long range of the weapon is tripled but it is not possible to add dice to the attack damage.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><em><strong>Lethal impact.</strong></em> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A critical shot from a firearm inflicts 1d6 levels of exhaustion.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><em><strong>Malfunctioning.</strong></em> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If the firearm was recharged under conditions of particular pressure or while in motion, missing the next shot to hit means causing the gunpowder to explode badly, suffering a level of weakness from the burn.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><em><strong>Wet powders.</strong></em> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Gunpowder can lose its effectiveness when wet, in rainy weather or other similar eventualities. If such opportunities arise and the character has not been able to perform maintenance, the character must make a DC 12 check on Intelligence before making the first hit. Failing that, the hit will fail and half the ammunition will be spoiled<br /></span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><em><strong>Complex recharge.</strong></em> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Recharging a firearm requires an action and not to make a movement during your turn. Moving during Recharge or being under particular pressure can cause Malfunctioning. </span></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Furthermore, you can just perform a single attack </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">with these firearms.</span></p>",
      "chat": "",
      "unidentified": ""
    },
    "source": "Historia Manuale pagina: 249",
